author: rezzim
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2020
review_content: I got this because the front door is un level and very drafty. I didn’t want to spend a lot since we rent it but the amount of bugs coming from underneath was annoying.The material is very flexible and pliable which is great. A lot of these that I’ve used at big box stores tend to be somewhat rigid and want to fall off the minute you open the door. For my application, the door itself is raised up about 2” from the floor, so I didn’t have to worry about it dragging. However the door is 90 years old so it’s seen a lot of wear and tear but this thing works perfectly. So impressed with how easy it was to apply, you can guide it along as you need to since it’s so flexible. I never thought I’d get excited about a door draft stopper but this is that moment. I fully don’t expect the adhesive to hold in my application simply because parts of the door are coming off and paint is flaking. But, I’ll put some staples in and call it a day. The adhesive is VERY strong much like the 3M double sided sticky tape. Much better than any other adhesive I’ve seen on door draft stoppers. Plus it comes in a two pack!!! Which clearly I did not read - bonus!!!It was so easy even my dog was able to help me install it. Although she was frustrated in this picture because she thought I was going to let her out instead of posting an Amazon review.
title: Well worth the price!

author: Raymond Wert II
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2020
review_content: I have one of them doors that nothing sticks to so I was apprehensive about buying this weather strip. It was very easy to install just clean the surface of the door, measure twice with it straightened out, cut to size and apply it after taking the tape off and voilà. Its very sticky and holds great.. I applied it very low to the carpet with no clearance and it rubs against the carpet but maintains its adhesion. I chose the 2-pk just in case but it doesnt look like im going need it so far after a couple weeks of use. I would definitely recommend this particular brand and item for a great product and price.
title: Great item

author: Barbara Klapper
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2020
review_content: We recently replaced some carpet in our house with wood floors and found that 2 of our doors were just too high off the floor. I work from home and the noise level from other areas of the house was too much. I would  close the door but found that was not much help. Rather than replace the doors, I decided to try these door draft stoppers. To my surprise and pleasure they worked perfectly to reduce the amount of noise coming from the other rooms.They are very easy to cut to size and easy to apply. For one door, I got the strip a little too high on the door and was worried that taking it off again would remove the paint on the door and probably would never stick again. I was wrong on both counts. The strip came off easily without taking off any paint and went back on securely. I am very happy with this product. I have yet to try these on the outside doors as I will need to remove the old hardware first, so I cannot attest to whether or not they do well to prevent drafts. That is my next project, as for now I know they are exactly what I wanted for the inside doors. They look beautiful on the doors (you can hardly tell they are there), they are very easy to assemble and they do a great job of reducing the light and noise.
title: Easy to cut, easy to adjust, stay secure and reduce light and noise

author: Liza
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2020
review_content: We actually bought this to block the air/smoke entering our apartment. My neighbor smoke so bad and we can smell when I’m standing at my door. It does a good job though of blocking the air. It blends on the color of our door. Price was reasonable and arrived earlier than expected.
title: Easy to install

author: Ray Purchase hates Toast
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 2, 2020
review_content: Have a storm door that lost part of its little rubber bottom strip caused by heavy use. The door is white, so this looks as if it came with it after being cut to fit. Be sure to clean and dry the area before using. I did have to reposition it a bit during install, but it has held its adhesion. Not bad for the price.
title: A nice and cheap alternative.

author: mystals1
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2020
review_content: I dont know why I didnt buy this earlier. My cat has been reaching under my bathroom door slowly tearing up the carpet. I'd show a picture of what she did but I'm afraid I'm too embarrassed. I was literally using duct tape to cover the hideous fringes she created and even that didnt stop her. Now I know what a carpet's skeleton looks like mixed into a ball made of shredded duct tape and sprinkled kitty litter. Gross. But anyways, that did the trick! THANK YOU!!
title: No More Duct Tape!!!!!

author: Rob
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2020
review_content: This door draft stopper is exactly what I needed for an external door going outside from my sun room.  My door had a draft stopper mounted underneath the door but when I cut it exactly 3 feet I ended up with a 1/2" between the door and the door jam.  This allowed a slight opening between the weather stripping and the bottom door draft stopper.  I cut this one slightly over 3 feet to cover that extra gap which fit perfectly.  No more light and no more bugs can crawl in.
title: Good Flexibility and Seal

author: Tammy S.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2021
review_content: Trust  me over the years I've learned to dig in deep to clean things with alcohol & let dry thoroughly before trying to stick anything to it.  This stuck with some painters tape tightly twice wrapped around my door to keep it in place to sit over night to I guess "cure".  Not only did this thing not help even to block drafts when I removed the PAINTERS TAPE the dang thing started lifted. Before someone suggests that it was the way I tore the tape off....NAH.  Don't go there.  I usually don't leave bad reviews but this really disappointed me especially when I thought it might help me keep some cold air out, warm air in, Maybe if it stayed on the door I really don't know.
title: Sorry I hated these things

author: Savvy Buyer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2020
review_content: It was an excellent product. Was really easy to install it. One small issue though is there is an overlap in the adhesion midway and it gets a little frustrating to even it out. But, once you get past that, it does what it is supposed to. The price is really worth it. I have a door mat next to the door. The strip easily bends to accommodate for the additional thickness of the mat and when the door is closed, the strip sits snug. I've been punting this work for a while and I am glad I finally got to it.
title: Must have if you feel the draft from under the door

author: Jerry
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2020
review_content: First of all this looks good on a picture but it’s pretty cheap quality uneven molding.I have never seen the worst quality molding in my life go to Home Depot and spent five dollars for a nice molding stay away from this seller of course made in China
title: DO Not Buy!!POOR QUALITY CHINA

author: Ursula Keene
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2020
review_content: Ok. I was in the middle of writing a paper until I realized how hot it was in the house. It was freezing in here last night. The only thing I've done differently is stuck this product to the bottom of the door. I live in an older house where the front and back door have gaps that let in a lot of air, and apparently it was allowing alot of cold air into the house. I can't vouch for its durability since it's only been up a few hours and I haven't used the door much, but air is no longer coming through the bottom of the doors, so I am a  happy and satisfied customer.* updated to add: is been a few days and I stuck a piece to the top of my front door too. It's cut down the air significantly and I'm pretty sure it's enough to keep the rain from coming through the door too.
title: If works!

author: AJ
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2020
review_content: Garbage! Save your money!Sticks for about 3 mins. as long as you don't open or close the door. This was a 2 pack. It trims to fit easily enough. Doesn't stick on interior or exterior. Manufacturers know this so they have included some little plastic thumb-tacs to nail in place. Very unsightly.
title: Doesn't adhere. Save your money!

author: Lesley  B
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2020
review_content: Was hard to peel off the red strip - had to peel some of the adhesive to get it to start to peel. Did not work on outside of door because would get caught on sides when closed and then flopped off. Adhesive very weak, so wouldn't stick to door no matter what I did. Followed instructions and was useless. Ended up in my trash. Wasted money and time.
title: Worthless

author: Linda  Sipple
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2020
review_content: Helps keep my cool air in so it doesn't escape the door. Easy to cut to size and apply. Much better than the old one I had put on 2 yrs ago. This also keeps the bugs out.
title: Easy to install & keeps cool air in bugs outside.

author: Robin S
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2020
review_content: The red strip that you ate supposed to take off before you put it on the door, does not come off. Very poor instructions.as well. Measure, cut, take off the strip and attach. Doesn't tell you how the strip is to come off.
title: The red strip doesn't come off

author: AG
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2021
review_content: I have tried everything provided and then some to get these to adhere to the doors and they all peeled off after a couple days. I even mounted it on and the edges started to get in the way of the door and damaged the door jam and floor in the process. All around, extremely disappointed in this product as I had high hopes initially and was thrilled to feel the difference. Then it turned into a nightmare. DON'T FALL FOR THIS.
title: THESE WILL NOT STAY ON!

author: Kelly R.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2020
review_content: I'm so happy I bought this product!Our apartment entry door and closet door both had large, unsightly gaps beneath them.We've tried door draft socks and the double sided draft guard (which was also double the price) we were using was all beat up and never stayed in place!This was such an easy installation! Just measure and trimmed to the length needed and stick to the bottom of the doors! We did use the matching tacs that came with to reinforce the adhesive.It looks really nice now! It's great not having to constantly fix or adjust what we had in it's place before these strips! It blocks the foyer light and anything else from coming under our door! And the second strip makes our closet door appear to be the correct size!Great product! Highly recommend!!
title: Such an easy installation, great product!

author: Jessica
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2020
review_content: I had a little gap under the door and tried several thresholds/weather stripping and the door wouldn’t shut. I decided to give this a try and....voila!  problem solved! It was so easy to put on! No more gap, and keeps little bugs out!
title: Does the job!!

author: James
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 29, 2020
review_content: Junk product. Adhesion is horrible. Just more junk.
title: Junk product

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2020
review_content: I've bought two packs so far (white and grey), and the colors blend well/don't stand out too much. If you find the stopper is too long for the door, they're easy to cut with regular scissors (I'd suggest using a ruler and a pencil so you cut the right amount). Applying is quick! You should clean the section you'll be applying, but also dust around the floor as the adhesive may pick up some unwanted dust/hairs. Even if you put it on and find it's not aligned or want it at a different height, you can easily remove and re-apply.I will caution (and only downside): if you're renting you may end having to pay to fix up the bottom of the door (if the landlord needs it removed) as the adhesion is very, very strong and will remove some of the door's paint.Pro: it will stay attached to a metal stopper! My current apartment came with a metal door stopper drilled into the bottom of the door (but not long enough to be effective). The grey stopper not only sticks to the metal, but still has enough length to make up the space that was left under the door.
title: Easy to apply, but may damage aftewards

author: Cdyana
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2020
review_content: I couldn't figure out how flies were getting inside my home. Just out of the blue one would zip by. Repeatedly checked all the doors and windows making sure everything was closed. As it turned out there was a very small gap at the bottom of one of the screen doors. I put one of these at the bottom of that door and problem solved. Easy to cut down. Easy to install.  If I ever need these again, I would definitely repurchase.
title: Problem Solved

author: K. Schwartz
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2021
review_content: We replaced our flooring to hard wood instead of fluffy carpet, which left 2 inches at the bottom of all doors.  I really don’t like that as when I am trying to sleep any lights that come on in the house glows into my dark bedroom and wakes me instantly.  I finally talked my husband into letting me add these to the bottom of the door.  Finally I can sleep without getting woken by the sudden glowing light shining in when the kids need to use the bathroom right outside our door.  It also makes it a little bit quieter.  These are easy to install, easy to cut off the extra with scissors, and they stick with no problems.  I had to take it off the first time and redo it because it was so tight to the floor it would drag when we closed the door and make a horrible sound against the laminate.  But it was easy to peel off and actually sticks fine a second time.  I did follow the directions and clean the area first.  Really glad I tried these.  One note, if you need air circulation between the room you may want to leave slight gap on end or not go clear to the floor.  Still a huge improvement!
title: Easy to install and actually works

author: Sapphyre
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2020
review_content: I bought this to seal up a gap along the bottom of my glass storm door, which may have been the reason why random mosquitos were getting in the house. As it turns out, this gap may have also been the way a smallish snake gained entry into the house. Ugh. While it's hard to know for sure how it got in, the gap at this door is now closed for business to outside pests. The draft stopper was very easy to apply and simple to cut into the proper length. I was worried it would look tacky, but it is barely noticeable. I used a white strip on the silver aluminum bottom portion of the door. A plus, too, that it will take care of drafts when cold weather returns. Delivery was also very fast. All in all, I'm very pleased.
title: Easy to apply and looks good

author: VonVon
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2020
review_content: adhesive not good - doesn't stay on doorwaste of money
title: Does not work well as advertised

author: Natalie Johnson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2020
review_content: I got this to use on my apartment door, we went through both of them within a couple months because they both fell off. I made sure to clean the door and dry completely before applying the way instructions said.
title: Didn't stick

author: Amelanchier
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2021
review_content: After replacing our metal/rubber door plates with these silicone strips, we were delighted that opening/closing the door was quieter. The original door plates were unsatisfactory. In fact, three baby garter snakes entered the house through these metal/rubber door plates.We were pleased with the new silicone plates for these reasons:1. Less drafty2. Quieter3. Easy installation4. Fits both sides of doorHowever, our rescue cat likes these, too. He chews on them at night. See photos for a demonstration: he photobombed the picture. Time to buy more natural rubber pacifiers for him.These are a better fit and quieter than the originals. I just wish my cat wasn’t inclined to tear them apart.
title: Avoid If You Have a Chewer

author: Betsy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2021
review_content: My front door has a gap 3/4" in some places along the side. I know this is for the bottom but I needed it for the side.  I wiped the wood down with alcohol, let it dry & stuck it on. It took both strips. They cut very clean & easy. I left a little opening where the door chain goes. It isn't big enough to notice. I did bring it up a little to go over the top & a bit on the bottom. It's been 4 to 6 degrees here at night. I can walk by the door without a windy chill.
title: Works GREAT

author: alethea henderson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2020
review_content: Your browser does not support HTML5 video.           After we had a new front door installed I noticed as the weather got cooler that it was a little drafty at the bottom. I've always kept a rug at the front door so never really noticed it. After installing this and putting my rug back in place and opening the door it now pushes the rug out of the way. I need to find a different type rug a lot thinner then the jute rug I have their now. But in general the product does keep the drafty air from coming in. I'm happy.
title: Works great!

author: Jorie West
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2020
review_content: Well, what do you know?  It works!  I followed the instructions and installed these strips on 5 doors in a very short time.  I even put it along the vertical side of one of my doors that does not fit properly and the atomosphere quickly changed in the room. They look just fine....nobody even notices them. I am very pleased.
title: Changed the atmosphere in my home

author: VB Mom
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2020
review_content: We have an older home with a great screened in porch but the wooden door to the outside has a large gap that bugs were walking under. I bought this because it was cheap and I didn’t care what it looked like. It has fixed the huge gap and less bugs get in. The gap wouldn’t be fixed completely  without replacing the door but this fixes it to my liking.The adhesive didn’t completely hold the strip on soI had to use the thumbtacks to hold it up. This worked because my door is made of older wood and I didn’t care about “damaging” an old door. This wouldn’t work for more solid wood doors (think a decorative front door).
title: Fit my needs!

author: Mountain Home
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2021
review_content: Big air gap at the bottom of the front door I needed to close up so I ordered this product.  I followed the directions and it applied as advertised.  I knew this was only a temporary solution until I could have a new door sweep professionally installed, but I was disappointed that this was not as good at sealing off the air as I had hoped.  I made sure it was all the way to the floor and ran the entire length of the door, but the bottom seems to fold under a little, necessitating I still lay a draft stopper along the seam to stop air coming in.  So, not horrible, but not a perfect solution by any means.
title: Not as good an insulator as i had hoped

author: mike's honest reviews
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 8, 2021
review_content: I just got done applying one to my back door, and this is why i only gave it 4 stars; when i peeled off the red strip that backs the adhesive, the adhesive came off with it. I noticed this when I'd already destroyed half the adhesive strip, but was able to salvage eough to apply it to my satisfaction. Time will tell if it works, but I can always apply some other supertape to it before it falls off. As to its longevity, I cant predict it but it is made of a very fine durable rubber and looks sturdy and it ISN'T one of those screw in types that I can never get to fit because I have a high door jamb. And I was in a hurry so it's probably my fault the adhesive came off, but I usually don't mess things up like that so BEWARE!!!UPDATE: It's been a few days and the thing is holding fast to the door, so I have to say this is a good product I recommend.
title: Watch it when you peel off the backing!!

author: Stephanie
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 16, 2020
review_content: I bought this primarily because there was a large gap on the bottom of my door and since its a two door it doubles the noise, of course I can still hear some things but they're very faint, as a streamer this helps greatly.

author: Annette Sherrer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2021
review_content: This is the first review I am excited about writing. I love these. The weather striping under my back door was not keeping out the cold air this winter.  We were freezing. I  bought two other brands and they didn't work so I got these.  I placed one on each side of the door.  What a difference they made.  It warm in my downstairs area.  So easy to install. Bought more to put on the front door. The adhesion is very good. Open abd close the back door multiple times during the day letting the dog out. They never have come off. Awesome!

author: Kaitlin
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2020
review_content: I bought this as an easy way to seal up our front door which was obviously installed incorrectly and left a pen width hole at the bottom of the door. They stick on great and I have not seen one bug since! Great purchase, would definitely recommend.
title: Keep those bugs out!

author: Greg D.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2021
review_content: Save your money; theses door draft stoppers are junk; very flimsy &  soft; they ship two per pack & fold them up so they are gonna have bends & kinks in them; I tried to lay them out for weeks & still see the bend marks; never installed & passes return date !!!Amazon will not refund because I passed the return date by one day ?? Ok now it’s on !!!It’s the principle!!!  I tried to get these kinks out & needed time !!! Never again I will send junk back the same day of delivery from now on !!! Junk junk junk !!!

author: RV Geezer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 16, 2020
review_content: Installation needs some prethought, as one doesn't want to overly distort the sweep line of the draft stopper, but should have mild contact with floor or entry base in order to work.  Installation should be done with the temperature over 60 degrees.  The adhesive is a bit forgiving in that it permits a bit of repositioning.  Mine is installed on the inside of my back door, and on the inner base of the storm door there.  I've been well pleased with the results of several weeks of use....and will move my rating up to 5 stars if it continues to function well through the winter.
title: Seems to work well

author: Mrs.Derrick
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2020
review_content: This was very easy to use and the stickiness is plenty... You can even reposition within a few minutes before sticky sets it's grip. Easy to cut to size also. I used the cut pieces to sort of patch gaps i found around the floorboards. Feels very siliconey.! I thought product would be a tad bit stiffer but it's bendable quality works too & looks good too. Came with 5 round push tacks also which helps keep product in place as you measure or position to your liking. I bought 2sets
title: Good Product

author: Anonymous
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2021
review_content: After many searches I came upon this product and I am not a “window shopper” so once I saw this product I instantly bought it, again and again.I even cut the extra overage to use in other places and luckily for me, my white home is white and bright so no more eye sores jammed on the bottom covering up the wind coming in, ability for neighbors to hear my phone conversations etc., and it looks lovely!It can also be used on the top of your doors and, on the sides. author: Sean M Flanagan

Exactly what I was looking for I have a metal door so a typical weather strip was not an option screwing into the door so this just sticks to the door can’t be any easier. Highly recommend.

author: thatlinuxdude

author: Judy

author: Amazon Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2020
review_content: My interior closet doors have about a 1/2” gap under them and my cats are constantly clawing at the carpet around this gap trying to see what’s on the other side of the door.This weather stripping is the perfect solution to seal this threshold gap and keep the cats attention away from the carpet in this area.This was so easy to cut to fit the precise area I needed and so far seems to be adhering very well to the door itself.

author: Luke wood
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2021
review_content: My wife and I didn't originally buy this for keeping the draft at bay. They work great as they are stiff enough to not let the cat push her toys through but soft enough not to damage our floors. We had no issues installing them and they have stayed on the doors ever since.  After seeing how well they worked we did buy a second set and used it on our front door and it helped keep the temperature of our living room more constant and our heater has turn on less often. Our heating bill went down a few dollars and I think they were well worth the investment.
title: Great for more than keeping the cold out.

author: Lisa J. Sellers

review_content: The adhesion made it very easy to attach it to the door, which really made a huge difference with the cold air coming underneath. However, the little tacks you used to securely adhere it to your door ,half of them the nail part just bent ,so we couldn't use them. East to install.

author: H.W.

author: MM

author: Nick

review_content: The ones that I got were not this dark brown, which would work well for it to blend with the door we have, but a very light brown, like cocoa with milk, which makes it look just like an out of place piece of cheap plastic. Got it refunded.
